content_vision: You contacted me in social media. We met. We came friends. We kissed, and we became lovers.
text:
Verse 1:
i gotta switch up my girl, she ain't right,
damn she got me feeling tight,
all i need is a girl who's true,
who won't make me wanna yell 'chair! ' at you.
feelin' like you need to confess, get down with the victim
hold your head high, and turn yourself in, don't be a victim.
yo, tell the bros, go get that shit,
no time to sit, we gotta hit licks,

Pre-Chorus 1:
i started at the bottom, with no cash to spend,
now i'm on top, they can't even comprehend.

Chorus 1:
she promised she could change your life, but it's all a lie,
your girl wants me cause i got them toys, make her feel alive.
runnin' from the drama, yeah i pop a pill
keepin' it real, head up in the hills.

Verse 2:
making big bread, while you're just a peasant,
ain't got time for your games, don't need no crescent.
this is what we do, we rock shows, we stay at the top,
we'll never be apart, forever we'll unlock our hearts.
constantly fighting these thoughts, please save me from my mind
but my lungs stay full, ready for a new day, that's my grind.
my life's insane, ain't no lie,
never been ordinary, you know who am i.

Pre-Chorus 2:
back when we was just living, on the streets, no doubt,
probably running up the score, just trying to make it out.

Chorus 2:
feelin' optimistic, my future is bright
gonna send you some love, no need for an email tonight.
listen up, just take it from me
if you want revenge, you gotta time it perfectly.

Bridge:
until then, we can't think straight,
do i stay or do i fall, is it too late?
through the struggle, we're just tryna find our way
but like a stormbringer, we'll come crashing down, no delay.

Outro:
i come in silence, but you know i'll make noise
not her, she's different, ain't no playboy toys

active_struct.name: The Progressive Motion
attrs: has a strong intro and verse-chorus development
allows for multiple prechoruses and choruses
suitable for longer songs with a bigger story arc

struct_suggs.name: The Rollercoaster Ride
attrs: well balanced structure with alternating verses and choruses
includes a bridge for variation and buildup
suitable for shorter songs

struct_suggs.name: The Progressive Motion

allows for multiple prechoruses and choruses
suitable for longer songs with a bigger story arc

struct_suggs.name: The Unconventional Journey
attrs: has a gradual buildup with the use of prechoruses
allows for instrumental sections and a bridge for variety
suitable for songs with a buildup to a final chorus or climax

struct_suggs.name: The Surprising Twist
attrs: has a strong intro and gradual buildup with the use of prechoruses
includes a bridge and instrumental sections for variation
suitable for longer songs and allows for multiple verse-chorus repetitions

struct_suggs.name: The Instrumental Adventure
attrs: has a unique structure with an instrumental section before the bridge
suitable for songs with a strong instrumental component
gives a sense of buildup and climax with the use of two choruses before the bridge

struct_suggs.name: The Dancefloor Anthem
attrs: has a strong and straightforward intro
suitable for shorter songs with a traditional verse-chorus structure
allows for variation with a bridge and multiple chorus repetitions

struct_suggs.name: The Dual Narrative
attrs: includes prechoruses for a gradual buildup
suitable for songs with a strong focus on vocals and harmonies
allows for variation with a contrasting second chorus

struct_suggs.name: The Epic Saga
attrs: has a strong intro and gradual buildup with the use of prechoruses
includes a bridge and multiple choruses for variation
suitable for longer songs and allows for multiple repetitions of the verse-chorus structure

struct_suggs.name: The Build-Up and Breakdown
attrs: has a unique structure with an instrumental section and bridge in the middle of the song
suitable for songs with a buildup to the final chorus
allows for repetition of the main chorus and a sense of climax in the outro

struct_suggs.name: The Climactic Finale
attrs: has a strong intro and gradual buildup with the use of prechoruses
includes a bridge and instrumental sections for a variety in the song
suitable for longer songs and allows for multiple verse-chorus repetitions

Verse 1:
so much talk about liberty, but she just rockin' that chanel
spouted out that freedom, but the time is now, can't you tell?
baby you stalling, ain't no time to waste
and we're all a little broken, but we still ace.
down to the river we'd ride, just you and me
no scammer gonna come between, we'll ride free.
you thought he was sleepin soundly, but
he been around the world, hustlin' non- stop.

Pre-Chorus 1:
my life's like a movie, all this drama
ain't talkin' bout no fancy sushi, just real commas

Chorus 1:
everybody say love, we gotta spread it all over
you know we got the courage to solve em, we never cower
oh my brother, we got each other and that's all we need.
run through five, i count my wins

Verse 2:
i had to beat the game quick, always on the hustle
but the lonely one warned me, gotta be ready for the struggles.
i'm out here grindin', you know where i be
advocating for the real ones, that's the life for me.
we can't seem to get far enough from this pain,
but maybe someday we'll find an understanding in vain.
we been grinding and hustling all the nights,
now it's time to blow up this house and take flight.

Pre-Chorus 2:
ruling like i'm genghis khan up in this game,
people tryna say i'm acting black, such a shame.

Chorus 2:
just be the one to see my flaws,
then we'll hurry on back to the hotel room, no applause.
we ball out, living lavish, that's just how we do,
'cause this is the place to be, where dreams come true.

Bridge:
climbing up the charts, reaching new heights,
so why bother with all the petty fights.
you gonna turn and walk away from me now?
fine, i'll take my glasses off, i won't allow.

Outro:
i'm the king of this game, you know
that's why you gon get that bitch cut, not just for show.

Verse 1:
she gave me the love of my life, she's my ride or die
infiltration, we don't let anyone come between you and i
and yeah, probably marge, she don't understand our real high.
there's so much more inside, we'll never be lone,
we made it on our own, and our bond has only grown.
i don't know why people fall in love,
got a mother but she ain't got enough,
so we'll just blow through 100 grand, feeling rough.

Pre-Chorus:
got my homie comin' through with the beat,
we'll make this track bump like we're on repeat.

Chorus:
we still doin' it baby, fuck the haters
be the one to see my flaws, fuck the debaters
we don't care, we still fuckin' with the gs.
gotta keep pushing, can't let myself stall,

Verse 2:
on the run, gotta take ten paces, gotta keep moving
but you won't get the heat off your chest, can't stop the grooving.
i went through a hundred bodies, no worries,
we were getting lit off the carti.
sippin' on champagne, feelin' like a king,
everyone got coke up in their nose, livin' like a star,
so i'mma treat myself, gonna buy a brand new car.
sylvie says she loves me, it's true,

Pre-Chorus 2:
they all claim to have your back, but they bitches,
when it comes down to it, they'll ditch you in a pinch,

Chorus 2:
she got that icebox drip on her wrist, drippin' cold
and that's why we both feel at home, we're cut from the same mold.
we move in silence, no need to make a sound,
and when you need to find me, i'll always be around.

Bridge:
i think to myself, they just can't keep track,
they slip and slide, can't keep up, if you would just relax.
young and old, we go back like crew cuts,
my boy green always got that good stuff, no ifs or buts.

Intro:
the cops can't even break in, we're untouchable,
would you stay with me, run the world, unstoppable?

Verse 1:
i just want what's real, that's all i need,
and she got a fat ass with a brain that'll make me breathe.
my shawty bad, she's got it all,
keep on bouncin', baby, we'll have a ball.
we stacking bands, ain't got no time for them,
the time is now, ion got no friend,
gotta grind hard, can't afford to pretend.
we got real people in the house, feeling the flow

Pre-Chorus 1:
everybody suffers, it's just the way of life
but we ball like that, we don't let it cause strife

Chorus 1:
we intertwine in pleasure, but it comes with pain,
they ain't ready for the love, they been training in vain.
he stayed back at the hotel, said he'd call, but i know he lied,
you can hide, but i'll find you, can't run away from the truth inside.

Verse 2:
my mind's always racing, constantly on the brink,
if you would, join me, let's spark a chemical reaction and link.
we flyin' into the sunset, make 'em all jealous,
they blushin' 'cause they can't handle us, gettin' down with it, gettin' rebellious.
don't hit me with no surprises, i can't handle it,
one way love ain't enough for two to make it.
they'll try to ride with you, but they don't have a clue,
only i can keep up, 'cause i go crazy for you.

Pre-Chorus 2:
all day just sitting on my throne, ain't no stopping me
run up on my enemy, give them a taste of my flavor, destroys their identity.

Chorus 2:
you heard the rumors, you know my name,
just watch as i rise, see the sunrise, it's time to claim my fame.
it felt like we were soaring past the sky,
our love was a chemical reaction, too high.

Bridge:
solving equations, that's just simple algebra,
pop the shit, stay on top, we the new gods, ha.
oooooooh, that's some real stuff, authentic as can be
but while they passin' us by, they'll never know what it feels like to be free.

Outro:
i step back in, back at the bar,
living life like it's a hollywood blockbuster.

Intro:
my eyes are wet, teardrops running down to my chin,
would you stay to catch me, from falling off the edge again?

Verse 1:
drop down low, show them what you got,
get to stepping, they just dumb and dull,
everybody chasing money, but it's not all
that life's about, there's more to uncover.
you can't define yourself, gotta stay true,
and love god, that's the only path to choose.
all my shooters came from moscow, they'll protect me,
fighting for my dreams, 'cause ain't no one gonna reject me.

Pre-Chorus 1:
girl, your heart is all i need, can't you see?
all i ever wanted was the cash, living luxury.

Chorus 1:
hustling my ass off, for that paper chase
fly off in my jet, and remember those high school days
take a toke, let the memories dance as we escape.
your love takes me away, to a place i've never been

Verse 2:
feeling like a monster, gotta be murderous,
no time for mercy, all my haters are just nervous.
keep your chin up, gotta hold your head,
don't let the world bring you down, don't give in to dread.
you know we keep it real, tell it like it is,
and they think i'm just frontin', they don't know who i is,
just watch me now, i'll show 'em what's up.
in these dark times, gotta pray up, gotta keep faith,

Pre-Chorus 2:
you know the deal, now you can apply,
don't take it too serious, just a lighthearted joke, we don't want no scammer in our tribe.

Chorus 2:
three minutes from where manny got shot
teardrops on my face, but i won't stop
i run wild till the day that i drop.
my daughters won't be controlled by any man,

Bridge:
you know we always keep it real,
but my mistakes come at a high cost, still feel.
all your powers and fame gonna fade in this haze,
but we'll always remember the good times with the beatles' craze.

Outro:
uh uh uh uh we speedballin' on the highway,
or go far enough to find that understanding we crave.
